<DIV>
<A NAME="A2016FORM10-K_Q4PROJECT_HTM_SEC2EB06DA10E5BB795177ED41C0F4693">
</A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	14. Earnings/(Loss) Per Share
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	We compute earnings/(loss) per share using a two-class method, an earnings allocation method used when a company&#8217;s capital structure includes either two or more classes of common stock or common stock and participating securities. This method determines earnings/(loss) per share based on dividends declared on common stock and participating securities (i.e., distributed earnings), as well as participation rights of participating securities in any undistributed earnings.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Earnings/(loss) per share is computed using both basic shares and diluted shares. The difference between basic and diluted shares is that diluted shares include the dilutive effect of the assumed exercise of outstanding securities. Our stock options, stock-settled long-term performance awards and restricted stock units could have the most significant impact on diluted shares. The decrease in our basic shares is primarily due to repurchases of the Company&#8217;s Class A Common Stock.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Securities that could potentially be dilutive are excluded from the computation of diluted earnings per share when a loss from continuing operations exists or when the exercise price exceeds the market value of our Class A Common Stock, because their inclusion would result in an anti-dilutive effect on per share amounts.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The number of stock options excluded from the computation of diluted earnings per share because they were anti-dilutive was approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>

</DIV>

<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	15. Stock-Based Awards
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;25, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, the Company was authorized to grant stock-based compensation under its 2010 Incentive Compensation Plan (the &#8220;2010 Incentive Plan&#8221;), which became effective April 27, 2010 and was amended and restated effective April 30, 2014. The 2010 Incentive Plan replaced the 1991 Executive Stock Incentive Plan (the &#8220;1991 Incentive Plan&#8221;). In addition, through April 30, 2014, the Company maintained its 2004 Non-Employee Directors&#8217; Stock Incentive Plan (the &#8220;2004 Directors&#8217; Plan&#8221;).
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company&#8217;s long-term incentive compensation program provides executives the opportunity to earn cash and shares of Class A Common Stock at the end of three-year performance cycles based in part on the achievement of financial goals tied to a financial metric and in part on stock price performance relative to companies in the Standard &amp; Poor&#8217;s 500 Stock Index, with the majority of the target award to be settled in the Company&#8217;s Class A Common Stock. In addition, the Company grants time-vested restricted stock units annually to a number of employees. These are settled in shares of Class A Common Stock.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	We recognize stock-based compensation expense for these stock-settled long-term performance awards and restricted stock units, as well as any stock options and stock appreciation rights (together, &#8220;Stock-Based Awards&#8221;). Stock-based compensation expense was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$12.4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	$10.6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	$8.9 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Stock-based compensation expense is recognized over the period from the date of grant to the date when the award is no longer contingent on the employee providing additional service. Awards under the 1991 Incentive Plan and 2010 Incentive Plan generally vest over a stated vesting period or, with respect to awards granted prior to December 28, 2014, upon the retirement of an employee or director, as the case may be.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Prior to 2012, under our 2004 Directors&#8217; Plan, each non-employee director of the Company received annual grants of non-qualified stock options with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	-year terms to purchase
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	4,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;shares of Class A Common Stock from the Company at the average market price of such shares on the date of grants. These grants were replaced with annual grants of cash-settled phantom stock units in 2012, and, accordingly, no grants of stock options have since been made under this plan. Under its terms, the 2004 Directors&#8217; Plan terminated as of April 30, 2014.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In 2015, the annual grants of phantom stock units were replaced with annual grants of restricted stock units under the 2010 Incentive Plan. Restricted stock units are awarded on the date of the annual meeting of stockholders and vest on the date of the subsequent year&#8217;s annual meeting, with the shares to be delivered upon a director&#8217;s cessation of membership on the Board of Directors. Each non-employee director is credited with additional restricted stock units with a value equal to the amount of all dividends paid on the Company&#8217;s Class A Common Stock. The Company&#8217;s directors are considered employees for purposes of stock-based compensation.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Our pool of excess tax benefits (&#8220;APIC Pool&#8221;) available to absorb tax deficiencies was approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$25 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;25, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Stock Options
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The 1991 Incentive Plan provided, and the 2010 Incentive Plan provides, for grants of both incentive and non-qualified stock options at an exercise price equal to the fair market value (as defined in each plan, respectively) of our Class A Common Stock on the date of grant. Stock options have generally been granted with a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	-year vesting period and a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	-year term and vest in equal annual installments. Due to a change in the Company&#8217;s long-term incentive compensation,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;grants of stock options were made in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The 2004 Directors&#8217; Plan provided for grants of stock options to non-employee directors at an exercise price equal to the fair market value (as defined in the 2004 Directors&#8217; Plan) of our Class A Common Stock on the date of grant. Prior to 2012, stock options were granted with a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	-year vesting period and a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	-year term.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	No
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;grants of stock options were made in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. The Company&#8217;s directors are considered employees for purposes of stock-based compensation.
</FONT>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The total intrinsic value for stock options exercised was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$0.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$2.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The fair value of the stock options granted was estimated on the date of grant using a Black-Scholes valuation model that uses the following assumptions. The risk-free rate is based on the U.S. Treasury yield curve in effect at the time of grant. The expected life (estimated period of time outstanding) of stock options granted was determined using the average of the vesting period and term. Expected volatility was based on historical volatility for a period equal to the stock option&#8217;s expected life, ending on the date of grant, and calculated on a monthly basis. Dividend yield was based on expected Company dividends, if applicable on the date of grant. The fair value for stock options granted with different vesting periods and on different dates is calculated separately.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>

<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Long-Term Incentive Compensation
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The 1991 Incentive Plan provided, and the 2010 Incentive Plan provides, for grants of cash and stock-settled awards to key executives payable at the end of a multi-year performance period.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Cash-settled awards have been granted with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	-year performance periods and are based on the achievement of specified financial performance measures. Cash-settled awards have been classified as a liability because we incurred a liability payable in cash. There were payments of approximately $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Stock-settled awards have been granted with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	-year performance periods and are based on relative Total Shareholder Return (&#8220;TSR&#8221;), which is calculated at stock appreciation plus deemed reinvested dividends, and another performance measure. Stock-settled awards are payable in Class A Common Stock and are classified within equity. The fair value of TSR awards is determined at the date of grant using a market calculation simulation. The fair value of awards under the other performance measure is determined by the average market price on the grant date.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Compensation expense for TSR-based awards is recognized based on the fair value on the grant date using a Monte Carlo simulation model. Compensation expense for the other performance measure is based on the expected number of shares or cash to be delivered as of each reporting date.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Unrecognized Compensation Expense
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;25, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, unrecognized compensation expense related to the unvested portion of our Stock-Based Awards was approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$14 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and is expected to be recognized over a weighted-average period of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1.41
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;years.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Reserved Shares
</FONT>

<A NAME="eolPage98"></A>

</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	16. Stockholders&#8217; Equity
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Shares of our Company&#8217;s Class&#160;A and Class B Common Stock are entitled to equal participation in the event of liquidation and in dividend declarations. The Class B Common Stock is convertible at the holders&#8217; option on a share-for-share basis into Class&#160;A Common Stock. Upon conversion, the previously outstanding shares of Class B Common Stock that were converted are automatically and immediately retired, resulting in a reduction of authorized Class B Common Stock. As provided for in our Company&#8217;s Certificate of Incorporation, the Class&#160;A Common Stock has limited voting rights, including the right to elect
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	30%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of the Board of Directors, and the Class&#160;A and Class B Common Stock have the right to vote together on the reservation of our Company shares for stock options and other stock-based plans, on the ratification of the selection of a registered public accounting firm and, in certain circumstances, on acquisitions of the stock or assets of other companies. Otherwise, except as provided by the laws of the State of New York, all voting power is vested solely and exclusively in the holders of the Class B Common Stock.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	There were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	816,632
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;shares as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;25, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	816,635
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;27, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of Class B Common Stock issued and outstanding that may be converted into shares of Class&#160;A Common Stock.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Adolph Ochs family trust holds approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	90%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of the Class B Common Stock and, as a result, has the ability to elect
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	70%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of the Board of Directors and to direct the outcome of any matter that does not require a vote of the Class&#160;A Common Stock.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On January 14, 2015, entities controlled by Carlos Slim Hel&#250;, a beneficial owner of our Class A Common Stock, exercised warrants to purchase
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	15.9 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;shares of our Class A Common Stock at a price of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$6.3572
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;per share, and the Company received cash proceeds of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$101.1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;from this exercise. Concurrently, the Board of Directors terminated an existing authorization to repurchase shares of the Company&#8217;s Class A Common Stock and approved a new repurchase authorization of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$101.1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, equal to the cash proceeds received by the Company from the warrant exercise. As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;25, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, total repurchases under this authorization totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$84.9 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;(excluding commissions) and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$16.2 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;remained under this authorization. Our Board of Directors has authorized us to purchase shares from time to time, subject to market conditions and other factors. There is no expiration date with respect to this authorization.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	We may issue preferred stock in one or more series. The Board of Directors is authorized to set the distinguishing characteristics of each series of preferred stock prior to issuance, including the granting of limited or full voting rights; however, the consideration received must be at least $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	100
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;per share. No shares of preferred stock were issued or outstanding as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;25, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	We have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;reportable segment that includes The New York Times, NYTimes.com and related businesses. Therefore, all required segment information can be found in the Consolidated Financial Statements.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;Our operating segment generated revenues principally from circulation and advertising. Other revenues consist primarily of revenues from news services/syndication, digital archives, rental income, our NYT Live business, e-commerce and affiliate referrals.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<A NAME="A2016FORM10-K_Q4PROJECT_HTM_S647F033C9D005068AFDA9BFC5232FF2B">
</A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	18.&#160;Commitments and Contingent Liabilities
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Operating Leases
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Operating lease commitments are primarily for office space and equipment. Certain office space leases provide for rent adjustments relating to changes in real estate taxes and other operating costs.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Rental expense amounted to approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	$16 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. The approximate minimum rental commitments under noncancelable leases, net of subleases, as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;25, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;were as follows:
</FONT>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Restricted Cash
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	We were required to maintain
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$24.9 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of restricted cash as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;25, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$28.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;27, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, the majority of which is set aside to collateralize workers&#8217; compensation obligations.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Newspaper and Mail Deliverers &#8211; Publishers&#8217; Pension Fund
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:10PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In September 2013, the Newspaper and Mail Deliverers-Publishers&#8217; Pension Fund (the &#8220;NMDU Fund&#8221;) assessed a partial withdrawal liability against the Company in the gross amount of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$26 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;for the plan years ending May 31, 2012 and 2013 (the &#8220;Initial Assessment&#8221;), an amount that was increased to a gross amount of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$34 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in December 2014, when the NMDU Fund issued a revised partial withdrawal liability assessment for the plan year ending May 31, 2013 (the &#8220;Revised Assessment&#8221;). The NMDU Fund claimed that when City &amp; Suburban Delivery Systems, Inc., a retail and newsstand distribution subsidiary of the Company and the largest contributor to the NMDU Fund, ceased operations in 2009, it triggered a decline of more than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	70%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in contribution base units in each of these two plan years.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:10PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company disagreed with both the NMDU Fund&#8217;s determination that a partial withdrawal occurred and the methodology by which it calculated the withdrawal liability, and the parties engaged in arbitration proceedings to resolve the matter. On June 14, 2016, the arbitrator issued an interim opinion and award that supported the NMDU Fund&#8217;s determination that a partial withdrawal had occurred, including concluding that the methodology used to calculate the Initial Assessment was correct. However, the arbitrator also concluded that the NMDU Fund&#8217;s calculation of the Revised Assessment was incorrect. The Company expects to appeal the arbitrator&#8217;s decision following the issuance of the final opinion and award.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:10PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Due to requirements of the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 that sponsors make payments demanded by plans during arbitration and any resultant appeals, the Company had been making payments to the NMDU Fund since September 2013 relating to the Initial Assessment and February 2015 relating to the Revised Assessment based on the NMDU Fund&#8217;s demand. As a result, as of December 25, 2016, we have paid
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$11.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;relating to the Initial Assessment since the receipt of the initial demand letter. We also paid
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$5.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;relating to the Revised Assessment, which was refunded in July 2016 based on the arbitrator&#8217;s ruling. Amounts recognized as expense were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$10.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;(including
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$6.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;resulting from the interim decision (see Note 9 for more information)),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$6.8 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$3.6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;for the fiscal years ended December 25, 2016, December 27, 2015 and December 28, 2014, respectively.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:10PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As a result of the interim opinion and award relating to the Initial Assessment, the Company had a liability of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$9.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;as of December 25, 2016. Management believes it is reasonably possible that the total loss in this matter could exceed the liability established by a range of zero to approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$10.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	P.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	98
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#32;&#8211; THE NEW YORK TIMES COMPANY
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
<A NAME="eolPage101"></A>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NEMG T&amp;G, Inc.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Company has been involved in class action litigation brought on behalf of individuals who, from 2006 to 2011, delivered newspapers&#160;at&#160;NEMG T&amp;G, Inc., a subsidiary of the Company (&#8220;T&amp;G&#8221;). T&amp;G was a part of the New England Media Group, which the Company sold in 2013. The plaintiffs asserted several claims against T&amp;G, including a challenge to their classification as independent contractors, and sought unspecified damages. In December 2016, the Company reached a settlement with respect to the claims. This settlement remains subject to court approval, and a final hearing is scheduled to take place in April 2017. As a result of the settlement, the Company recorded a charge of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$3.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in the fourth quarter within discontinued operations.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Other
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	We are involved in various legal actions incidental to our business that are now pending against us. These actions are generally for amounts greatly in excess of the payments, if any, that may be required to be made. Although the Company cannot predict the outcome of these matters, it is possible that an unfavorable outcome in one or more matters could be material to the Company&#8217;s consolidated results of operations or cash flows for an individual reporting period. However, based on currently available information, management does not believe that the ultimate resolution of these matters, individually or in the aggregate, is likely to have a material effect on the Company&#8217;s financial position.
</FONT>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

	of period

</FONT>
</DIV>

</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	EVALUATION OF DISCLOSURE CONTROLS AND PROCEDURES
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Our management, with the participation of our principal executive officer and our principal financial officer, evaluated the effectiveness of our disclosure controls and procedures (as defined in Rules 13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934) as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;25, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. Based upon such evaluation, our principal executive officer and principal financial officer concluded that our disclosure controls and procedures were effective to ensure that the information required to be disclosed by us in the reports that we file or submit under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 is recorded, processed, summarized and reported within the time periods specified in the SEC&#8217;s rules and forms, and is accumulated and communicated to our management, including our principal executive officer and principal financial officer, as appropriate to allow timely decisions regarding required disclosure.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	MANAGEMENT&#8217;S REPORT ON INTERNAL CONTROL OVER FINANCIAL REPORTING
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Management&#8217;s report on internal control over financial reporting and the attestation report of our independent registered public accounting firm on our internal control over financial reporting are set forth in Item&#160;8 of this Annual Report on Form 10-K and are incorporated by reference herein.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CHANGES IN INTERNAL CONTROL OVER FINANCIAL REPORTING
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	There were no changes in our internal control over financial reporting during the quarter ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	December&#160;25, 2016
</FONT>

<EFX_OTHER_INFORMATION>
<A NAME="FIS_OTHER_INFORMATION"></A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<DIV STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PX;TEXT-INDENT:0PX;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;PADDING-TOP:10PX;">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;WIDTH:260PX;BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN="1">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:260PX;">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;PADDING-LEFT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	ITEM&#160;9B.&#160;OTHER&#160;INFORMATION
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	On February 16, 2017, the Compensation Committee of the Company&#8217;s Board of Directors approved a form of Restricted Stock Unit Award Agreement (the &#8220;RSU Agreement&#8221;) to govern the terms of restricted stock units (&#8220;RSUs&#8221;) granted to employees under the Company&#8217;s 2010 Incentive Compensation Plan, as amended (the &#8220;Plan&#8221;). Under the terms of the RSU Agreement (and subject to the Plan), holders of RSUs will be entitled to receive one share of the Company&#8217;s Class A Common Stock per RSU upon the vesting thereof provided the holder remains continuously employed with the Company through the vesting date. RSUs vest in accordance with a vesting schedule specified at the time of grant. The RSU Agreement provides for the acceleration of vesting upon the holder&#8217;s death or Disability (as defined in the Plan), or upon the holder&#8217;s termination in certain circumstances within 12 months following a Change in Control (as defined in the Plan). Holders of RSUs are entitled to payments equal to dividends paid on the Company&#8217;s Class A Common Stock during the vesting period.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The foregoing summary of the RSU Agreement is incomplete and is qualified by reference to the form of RSU Agreement filed as an exhibit to this Annual Report on Form 10-K.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>

<EFX_DIRECTORS_AND_OFFICERS>
<A NAME="FIS_DIRECTORS_AND_OFFICERS"></A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<DIV STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PX;TEXT-INDENT:0PX;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;PADDING-TOP:10PX;">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;WIDTH:661PX;BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">

<TD COLSPAN="1">
</TD>

</TD>

<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;PADDING-LEFT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:HELVETICA,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#FFFFFF;">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The Board of Directors has adopted a code of ethics that applies not only to the principal executive officer, principal financial officer and principal accounting officer, as required by the SEC, but also to our Chairman. The current version of such code of ethics can be found on the Corporate Governance section of our website at http://investors.nytco.com/investors/corporate-governance. We intend to post any amendments to or waivers from the code of ethics that apply to our principal executive officer, principal financial officer or principal accounting officer on our website.

	Includes (i)&#160;4,517,832 shares of Class A stock to be issued upon the exercise of outstanding stock options granted under the 1991 Incentive Plan, the 2010 Incentive Plan, and the 2004 Non-Employee Directors&#8217; Stock Incentive Plan, at a weighted-average exercise price of $13.77 per share, and with a weighted-average remaining term of 3 years; (ii) 1,008,263 shares of Class A stock issuable upon the vesting of outstanding stock-settled restricted stock units granted under the 2010 Incentive Plan; (iii) 62,348 shares of Class A stock related to vested stock-settled restricted stock units granted under the 2010 Incentive Plan issuable to non-employee directors upon retirement from the Board; and (iv) 3,158,996 shares of Class A stock that would be issuable at maximum performance pursuant to outstanding stock-settled performance awards under the 2010 Incentive Plan. Under the terms of the performance awards, shares of Class A stock are to be issued at the end of three-year performance cycles based on the Company&#8217;s achievement against specified performance targets. The shares included in the table represent the maximum number of shares that would be issued under the outstanding performance awards; assuming target performance, the number of shares that would be issued under the outstanding performance awards is 1,579,498.

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	This Restricted Stock Unit Award Agreement (the &#8220;Agreement&#8221;) is made and entered into as of [GRANT DATE] (the &#8220;Grant Date&#8221;) between The New York Times Company, a corporation organized under the laws of the State of New York (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) and [PARTICIPANT NAME] (the &#8220;Participant&#8221;) pursuant to The New York Times Company 2010 Incentive Compensation Plan, as it may at any time hereafter be supplemented, modified, amended or restated (the &#8220;Plan&#8221;). Capitalized terms used in this document that are not otherwise defined have the meaning set forth in the Plan.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	1.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	General
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. Subject to the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and in the Plan, the Company hereby grants to the Participant [NUMBER] restricted stock units (the &#8220;RSUs&#8221;). Each RSU represents the right to receive one Share on the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and in the Plan.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	2.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Vesting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. Except as otherwise provided in Sections 4 and 5 below, the RSUs will vest in accordance with the vesting schedule set forth in the RSU Grant Detail made available electronically to the Participant on the Plan Website (as defined in Section 16 below) or otherwise (each such vesting date, a &#8220;Vesting Date&#8221;); provided that, the Participant is, on the applicable Vesting Date, and has been from the date of grant of the RSUs to the applicable Vesting Date, continuously employed by the Company or one of its Subsidiaries.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	3.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Delivery of Shares
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	. The Shares subject to the RSUs will be transferred upon or as soon as practicable after (but no later than 60 days after) the applicable Vesting Date to a brokerage account in the name of the Participant maintained with the administrative services provider of the RSUs (such provider from time to time, the &#8220;Administrative Services Provider&#8221;).
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	4.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Termination of Employment.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Upon termination of a Participant&#8217;s employment with the Company and its Subsidiaries as described below, the RSUs will be treated in the manner described below.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;PADDING-LEFT:72PX;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	(a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Death or Disability
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	: If a Participant&#8217;s employment with the Company and its Subsidiaries terminates by reason of the Participant&#8217;s (i) death or (ii) total disability (as defined by the terms of &#8220;The New York Times Companies Long-Term Disability Plan&#8221; or any successor long-term disability plan, whether or not the Participant is a participant in such long-term disability plan), all outstanding RSUs will vest and the Participant or his or her designated beneficiary will be entitled to receive the underlying Shares as soon as practicable thereafter (but no later than 60 days thereafter), subject to delayed delivery as may be required pursuant to Section 8.12 of the Plan.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;PADDING-LEFT:72PX;TEXT-INDENT:48PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	(b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Other Termination
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	: Subject to Section 5 below, on any other termination of the Participant&#8217;s employment, all RSUs held by such Participant will be immediately forfeited and the Participant will not have any right to delivery of the underlying Shares.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	5.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Change in Control
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	If pursuant to action taken under Section 7 of the Plan, a Participant&#8217;s RSUs that are outstanding at the time of a Change in Control are not to remain outstanding following the Change in Control and are not to be substituted with a new equity award, then, subject to the requirements of Section 409A of the Code, all of the Shares subject to such RSUs will be delivered to the Participant immediately prior to such Change in Control. If the RSUs are to remain outstanding following the Change in Control or are to be substituted with a new equity award, then, subject to the requirements of Section 409A of the Code, the portion of the RSUs or substituted equity award that remains outstanding but unvested at the time of the Participant&#8217;s termination of employment within 12 months following a Change in Control will become fully vested immediately prior to such termination, unless such termination is on account of the Participant&#8217;s voluntary resignation, willful and gross misconduct or willful failure to perform services for
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
<A NAME="eolPage113"></A>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	his or her employer. To the extent RSUs vest immediately prior to the Participant&#8217;s termination of employment pursuant to the preceding sentence, the Participant will be entitled to receive the underlying Shares as soon as practicable (but no later than 60 days following termination), subject to delayed delivery as may be required pursuant to Section 8.12 of the Plan.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	6.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Rights as a Stockholder; Dividend Equivalents.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;The Participant will not have the rights of a stockholder of the Company with respect to Shares subject to the RSUs until such Shares are actually delivered to the Participant. However, the Company will pay to each Participant holding RSUs on the record date of any cash dividend, an amount, per RSU held, equal to the amount of the cash dividend declared and paid in respect of one Share. This dividend equivalent will be included in each such Participant&#8217;s regular compensation for the pay period during which the actual cash dividend is paid, and will be subject to applicable withholding taxes.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	7.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	U.S. Federal, State and Local Income Withholding.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The Participant is solely responsible for the satisfaction of all taxes that may arise in connection with the RSUs. For U.S. citizens and residents (&#8220;U.S. Taxpayers&#8221;), the Shares when delivered will be taxable to the Participant at their then fair market value as ordinary income, subject to wage-based withholding and reporting. The Company will satisfy this withholding obligation by reducing the number of Shares to be delivered to U.S. Taxpayers in an amount sufficient to satisfy the withholding obligations due (based on the fair market value of the Shares); provided however, that no Shares will be withheld with an aggregate value exceeding the minimum amount of tax required to be withheld by law unless otherwise determined by the Committee prior to such withholding. The remaining Shares will be transferred to a brokerage account in the name of the Participant. For purposes of this paragraph, fair market value means the closing price of the Shares, as reported by the composite transaction reporting system for securities listed on the New York Stock Exchange (or such other national securities exchange on which the Shares may be listed at the time of determination), on the business day preceding the vesting date.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	8.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Section 409A.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The RSUs are intended to comply with Section 409A of the Code or an exemption thereunder and will be construed and interpreted in a manner that is consistent with and administered in accordance with Section 8.12 of the Plan. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Company makes no representations that the payments and benefits provided under this Agreement comply with Section 409A of the Code and in no event will the Company be liable for all or any portion of any taxes, penalties, interest or other expenses that may be incurred by the Participant on account of non-compliance with Section 409A of the Code.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	9.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Company Policies.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The RSUs, the underlying Shares, and any cash proceeds realized from the sale of such underlying Shares are subject to forfeiture or repayment to the Company pursuant to any &#8220;clawback&#8221; policy that the Company may have in place from time to time and are subject to any share trading policies and other policies that may be implemented by the Company from time to time.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	10.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	No Right to Employment.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	Neither the grant of RSUs, nor any other action taken hereunder shall be construed as giving the Participant the right to be retained in the employ or service of the Company or any of its Subsidiaries (for the vesting period or any other period of time), nor shall it interfere in any way with the right of the Company or any of its Subsidiaries to terminate the Participant&#8217;s employment or service at any time.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	11.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Other Benefits
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	No amount accrued or paid under the RSUs will be deemed compensation for purposes of computing a Participant's benefits under any retirement plan of the Company or its Subsidiaries, nor affect any benefits under any other benefit plan now or subsequently in effect under which the availability or amount of benefits is related to the Participant&#8217;s level of compensation.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:0PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;">
<FONT STYLE="PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;PADDING-RIGHT:24PX;">
	12.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Plan Provisions.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	The RSUs are being granted pursuant to the Plan, the terms of which are incorporated herein by reference, and will in all respects be interpreted in accordance the Plan. The grant and settlement of the RSUs are subject to interpretations, regulations and determinations concerning the Plan established from time to time by the Committee in accordance with the provisions of the Plan. The Committee shall have the authority to interpret and construe this Agreement, and the decisions of the
</FONT>
</DIV>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	No Assignment.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&#32;&#32;The RSUs may not be assigned or transferred by the Participant except to a Beneficiary in the event of the Participant&#8217;s death, to the extent that the RSUs survive the Participant&#8217;s death. Any other attempted assignment or transfer shall be null and void and shall extinguish, in the Company&#8217;s sole discretion, the Company&#8217;s obligation with respect to the RSUs and under this Agreement. The Company may assign the RSUs and this Agreement in accordance with the Plan.
</FONT>

The Participant has been provided a link to the Plan Website. 	The Participant will be asked by the Company to acknowledge this Award through the Plan Website.

</DIV>

	AMENDMENT NO. 2
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:174%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#1C1C1C;">
	THIS INSTRUMENT made as of the 11th day of November, 2016, by the ERISA Management Committee ("Committee") of The New York Times Company (the "Company").
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:232%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	W I T N E S S E T H
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:174%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#1C1C1C;">
	WHEREAS, the Company maintains The New York Times Companies Supplemental Retirement and Investment Plan, as restated January 1, 2015 (the "Plan"), as amended from time&#173; to time for the benefit of certain eligible employees; and
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:174%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#1C1C1C;">
	WHEREAS, pursuant to Section 12 of the Plan, the Committee has the authority to amend the Plan; and
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:174%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#1C1C1C;">
	WHEREAS, the Committee desires to amend the Plan to add Submarine Leisure Club, Inc. as a participating employer effective as of January 1, 2017;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:174%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#1C1C1C;">
	NOW, THEREFORE, the Plan is amended effective as of January 1, 2017 as follows:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:174%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:11PT;COLOR:#1C1C1C;">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>

</DIV>

</TR>

<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">

	(a)
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="3" STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities, particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">

</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD COLSPAN="3" STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BOTTOM;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">

<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Disclosed in this report any change in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#8217;s most recent fiscal quarter (the registrant&#8217;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting; and
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">

	5.
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:PALATINO,SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	(a)

<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	Based on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>
